{"lemma":"مُرَكَّب","slug":"مُرَكَّب","root":"ر.ك.ب","root_slug":"ر-ك-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ك-ب","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16480","n16481","n16482"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A8"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"anything upon which one rides; ship, boat, vessel"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"anything upon which one rides; saddle"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"compound, composed of multiple parts"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"compound"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Originally a noun of place meaning “place of riding”, from the verb رَكِبَ (rakiba, “to ride”). Cognate with Hebrew מֶרְכָּבָה (merkaḇa, “chariot”), Ge'ez መርከብ (märkäb), Classical Syriac ܡܰܪܟܰܒܬܳܐ.\n\nDerived from the passive participle of رَكَّبَ (rakkaba). Compare Hebrew מֻרְכָּב (murkáv, “complicated, complex”)."},"ipa":["/mar.kab/","/mu.rak.kab/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16480","headword_ar":"مَرْكَبٌ","root":"rkb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba","text_ar":"رَكِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, K, TA.) ―         -b2-  And also a noun of place [properly signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of riding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.) [Hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything upon which one rides;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in, which one is borne"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"carried:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAkib","text_ar":"مَرَاكِب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the land;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [more commonly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sea:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a beast"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on which one rides"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (A, TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a vessel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a ship"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh, Msb, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a saddle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any kind of vehicle borne by a camel or other beast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the lexicons passim:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAkibu","text_ar":"مَرَاكِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the pl. (Mgh, Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niEoma Almarokabu Ald~aAb~apu","text_ar":"نِعْمَ المَرْكَبُ الدَّابَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Excellent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most excellent, is the thing upon which one rides, the beast"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='ato maraAkibu Alyamani","text_ar":"جَا=ءَتْ مَرَاكِبُ اليَمَنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The vessels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the ships"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boats, of El-Yemen came."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b3-  [And hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almarokabu","text_ar":"المَرْكَبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as the name of (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The principal star"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Pegasus;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because in the place of the saddle.]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","A","Mgh","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n16481","headword_ar":"مُرْكِبٌ","root":"rkb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A colt"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has become fit for being ridden."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAb~apN murokibapN","text_ar":"دَابَّةٌ مُرْكِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A beast that has attained the age at which one may ride him during a warring and plundering expedition."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n16482","headword_ar":"مُرَكَّبٌ","root":"rkb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to whom a horse is lent for a portion of the spoil that he may obtain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA:) or a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who borrows a horse upon which to go forth on a warring and plundering expedition, and who receives one half of the spoil, the other half being for the lender:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to whom a horse has been given for him to ride, and who has put his foot into the stirrup."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) [Also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weak in the art of horsemanship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the management of horses, and the riding of them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 441.) ―         -b2-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Put,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"set, one part upon another: set,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fixed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in another thing:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"composed; constituted;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put together:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see its verb, 2.] The stone ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"set"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in the signet-ring is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"murak~abN","text_ar":"مُرَكَّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiybN","text_ar":"رَكِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and so the arrowhead ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fixed"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in the shaft: (S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiybN","text_ar":"رَكِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies, (K, TA,) as a subst., (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing set"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"murak~abN","text_ar":"مُرَكَّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"such as a ring-stone in the bezel, or collet, of the signet-ring. (K, * TA.)       -A2-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Origin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of growth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"germination"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vegetation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kariymu Almurak~abi","text_ar":"كَرِيمُ المُرَكَّبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is generous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble, in respect of the origin of his rank among his people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A. *)"}],"source_refs":["IAar","TA","K","S"]}]}}